    "Leaving the polished elegance of Ginkaku-ji behind, we approach the wide open space of the Kyoto Imperial Palace Park, where the echo of imperial history is mellowed by the surrounding natural beauty. This park, once the center of Japan's Imperial Family's life until the capital shifted to Tokyo in eighteen sixty-nine, now welcomes everyone seeking peace among its grass and trees, cleverly arranged following traditional Japanese garden style." /
